      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHECK IT OUT (1) has missed the placings at her last couple but was in the money three back when third (24.70) at this track in a Grade 5. Has the ability and looks a key chance here. DR. PARIS (5) scored a most impressive win two back then drifted back and missed the frame latest finishing a 5 length 4th at Warragul (26.23). Will give the top chances plenty to think about. OLIVER KELTON (2) turned in a better effort at this track last start, finishing second behind Paw Uma (24.64) in a Grade 5. Has the pace to be prominent. Some good form is emerging from his last run. Leading chance. TOMMY THE HOOD (7) looks a top-three chance while fresh.",
